extends ../layout

block content

  .marketing
    .row
      .col-lg-4
        i.img-circle.icon-th.icon-4x
        h2 Data-Grid
        p
          | Searchable, sortable, paginateable.
        p
          a.btn.btn-default(href="#datagrid") View details »
      .col-lg-4
        i.img-circle.icon-star.icon-4x
        h2 Commons
        p
          | Easy modals, styling and input sanitation.
        p
          a.btn.btn-default(href="#commons") View details »
      .col-lg-4
        i.img-circle.icon-link.icon-4x
        h2 Greppy Bindings
        p
          | Use Greppy resources, routing, interaction.
        p
          a.btn.btn-default(href="#bindings") View details »

    hr.featurette-divider
    a(name="datagrid")
    .featurette
      img.featurette-image.img-circle.pull-right(src="/modules/home/img/home/explore.png")
      h2.featurette-heading
        | Take a look at existing applications.&nbsp;
        span.text-muted Become interested.
      p.lead.
        To get a feeling for the ease of writing applications with Greppy
        you should try our demo application. It's got a frontend module, and
        a really easy REST service.

      p
        | Just read more on the GitHub&nbsp;
        a(target="_blank", href="https://github.com/Jack12816/greppy-demo") project page
        | .

    hr.featurette-divider
    a(name="commons")
    .featurette
      img.featurette-image.img-circle.pull-left(src="/modules/home/img/home/getting-started.png")
      h2.featurette-heading
        | Learn more about our concepts.&nbsp;
        span.text-muted You'll be excited.
      p.lead.
        You aren't content with the demo anymore?

      p
        | Study our concepts and learn all you need to write your own
        | Greppy-based application. The quickest way is via our&nbsp;
        a(target="_blank", href="/docs") documentation
        | .

    hr.featurette-divider
    a(name="bindings")
    .featurette
      img.featurette-image.img-circle.pull-right(src="/modules/home/img/home/contribute.png")
      h2.featurette-heading
        | Greppy is open source - contributions are welcome.&nbsp;
        span.text-muted Just read further on GitHub.
      p.lead.
        For getting you started to work on Greppy, read the documentation
        and watch for issues.
      p
      | If you plan to extend Greppy, the easiest way
      | would be to open an issue and discuss it. For feature requests it
      | would be the same. So take a look at&nbsp;
      a(target="_blank", href="https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo") GitHub
      | .


